      "question": "How do you select a customer segment when weighing market research against intrinsic motivation?",
      "answer": "Search for where you feel the deepest empathy — a problem you experienced, watched people you know experience, or contributed to creating. That feeling predicts whether you will sustain daily customer conversations, and it should anchor the choice alongside conventional sizing criteria.",
