      "qa_id": "transcript-evidence:icp-user-interviews-2026-05-27:qa:3",
      "question": "How do you reconcile committing to a narrow segment with taking creative risks?",
      "answer": "Pick a focus that is both sufficiently large and sufficiently sharp that you can still run experiments inside it; sequence the work so you get clean signal from a defined audience first, then let that audience grow rather than chasing every adjacent use case at once.",
