      "question": "How do you get honest feedback when demoing a live experience?",
      "answer": "Observe behavior rather than collecting opinions: watch whether people engage unprompted, whether they know what to do, and how their energy shifts. Reactions in the room are far harder to fake than written feedback, and live failures reveal what the audience actually values.",
